description: Adapted from the Latin aquaeductus (“conveyance of water”), from aqua (“water”) + dūcō (“I lead”, “I bring”); compare the French aqueduc.

entries.meaning: An artificial channel that is constructed to convey water from one location to another.
A structure carrying water over a river or depression, especially in regards to ancient aqueducts.
(anatomy) A structure conveying fluid, such as the cerebral aqueduct or vestibular aqueduct.
